  "text": "suggest that the most likely basis of the exaggerated phenotype in the GRK1 Ϫ/Ϫ mice is the strongly and persistently adapted state of the retina during the experiments rather than a \"loss of function\" of GRK1 in an inner retinal cell, because no GRK1 message or protein has been identified outside the photoreceptor layer (Figs. 1, 2 ). An interesting alternative hypothesis is that some \"miswiring\" of the retina may have occurred during development [CITATION_1] .",
